===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|つぶ|yomi=k}}
Not attested until a text from the Muromachi period with the spelling {{m|ja|3=ツブ|tr=tsubu}}.<ref name="KDJ2O_tubu"/>

An earlier form {{m-self|ja|粒|tr=tsubi}} exists, which might have been the predecessor to this word; both must have been ultimately derived from a source cognate to {{m|ja|つぶら|tr=tsubura|t=the state of being round and small|pos=obsolete}}.<ref name="KDJ2O_tubu"/><ref name="KDJ2O_tubi"/>

====Pronunciation====
* {{ja-pron|つぶ|acc=1|acc_ref=<ref name="KDJ2O_tubu">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten 2 Online|つぶ 【粒】|lid=200202d71281ZHrBe39v|kotobank=粒}}</ref>}}
* {{ja-accent-dialectal|k-0|つぶ|tsúbú|region=Kyoto}}<ref name="KDJ2O_tubu"/>

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|つぶ}}

# something [[round]] and [[small]], such as a [[kernel]] of [[grain]] or a [[bead]]
# the [[seed]] of a grain
# a [[black]], [[hard]] [[seed|seed]] obtained from the [[skin]] of a soapnut tree
# {{syn of|ja|無患子|tr=mukuroji|t=Indian soapberry ({{taxlink|Sapindus mukorossi|species}})}}
# a [[small]] [[change]] of [[coin|coins]]
# the [[bead]] of an [[abacus]]
# a [[person]] or [[thing]] who makes up a [[larger]] [[group]] of [[such]]
# a [[beat]] of a [[percussion]] [[instrument]] during [[performance|performances]] such as [[noh]] and [[nagauta]]
# a [[wig]] used in [[kabuki]] [[play|plays]] whose [[chignon]] is small and round
# {{syn of|ja|螺|tr=tsubu|t=pond snail|pos=now dialectal}}
# {{lb|ja|slang|gambling}} [[dice]]; [[die]]

