===Etymology 2===
{{ja-kanjitab|つび|yomi=k}}
From {{inh|ja|ojp|粒|tr=tubi₂}}, itself attested since the ''{{w|Shin'yaku Kegonkyō Ongi Shiki}}'' of 794:<ref name="KDJ2O_tubi">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten 2 Online|つび 【粒】|lid=200202d70e6062OlmODK|kotobank=粒}}</ref>
* {{ux|ojp
|数其滴 古経為<sub>二</sub>字<sub>一</sub>滴音宅、訓'''都飛'''<ref name="KDJ2O_tubi"/>
|The number of those kernels; in the old Buddhist sutras, the character {{m|zh|滴}} meaning "kernel" is to be read something like ''tek{{sic}}''; the native Japanese reading for this word is '''''tubi₂'''''.
}}

This word, along with {{m-self|ja|粒|tr=tsubu}}, must have been derived from a source cognate to {{m|ja|つぶら|tr=tsubura|t=the state of being round and small|pos=obsolete}}.<ref name="KDJ2O_tubi"/><ref name="KDJ2O_tubu"/>

